title: Archery World Record: Most arrows through a keyhole

media:group.media:title: Archery World Record: Most arrows through a keyhole
media:group.media:description:
Most difficult archery record ever made!
The purpose of my officially controlled record attempt, was to try make a record that could be compared to the heroic shots of historical super archers?

The record attempt was filmed with four cameras from different sides and the keyhole from the side in slow motion so you can see the arrow going into the keyhole (there is a small clip at the end of the video) but it looks coolest from the front Camera!!

Everyone can try it themselves, it just takes a keyhole so it's easy to try.

Bow: Şimşek Sipahi
Arrows: Carbon arrows without feathers (otherwise they won't go all the way through the keyhole)

I have been training for a long time to shoot through keyholes
so much so that up to the record attempt I dreamed of keyholes.

I just watched Dude Perfect’s Archery World record and it got me super excited!
I love it when archery gets attention and new world record really helps with that!
So big shoutout to Dude Perfect and James Jean and congratulations on the world record.

Lars Andersen
